To education matters now and university students are staring at a possible fee increase of up to three times after treasury cabinet secretary, Ukur Yattani, admitted that the current funding model is not sustainable. Yattani&rsquo;s budget statement on funding public universities is a true reflection of what vice chancellors have been pushing for. As Shadrack Mitty reports, tuition fee is likely to rise from the current 16, 000 to 48,000 shillings.
